The paper discusses the use of students as experimental subjects in software engineering research, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the external validity of student-based experiments, which is a concern in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) research. The paper also mentions basic programming and comprehension skills, which suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) research. The discussion of using students in the initial formative stages of large industrial research initiatives suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY) research. Finally, the paper discusses the use of students in educational settings, which suggests a focus on computer science education (cs.EDU) research.
